    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-04-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 304.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction No. 313 of the 21st
                    of February last in relation to Messrs. Arkell &amp; Douglas’s shipments to
                    South Africa by the <hi rend="italic">Maria, Mashona</hi>, and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Beatrice</hi>, I have the honor to inclose herewith copies of Mr. White’s
                    note to Lord Salisbury, of the 19th ultimo, and of the reply of the foreign
                    office thereto, of the 13th instant.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph H. Choate.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 1.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to the <gloss
                                type="to">Marquis of Salisbury</gloss>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-19">
                                <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>My <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord</hi>: With reference to the detention of
                        American merchandise by the British authorities in South Africa, I have the
                        honor, under instructions from my Government, to inclose for your lordship’s
                        information copies of bills of lading representing shipments made by Messrs.
                        Arkell &amp; Douglas, a firm of New York merchants, by the steamships <hi
                            rend="italic">Maria, Beatrice</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi>,
                        destined for Delagoa Bay.</p>
                    <p>It will be observed from the bills of lading above mentioned that the
                        shipments made by Messrs. Arkell &amp; Douglas, embrace all classes of
                        general cargo, such as kerosene oil, brooms, stoves, building materials,
                        white meal, shovels, turpentine, lard oil, plows, shellers, flour, etc.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 2.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bertie</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                            </placeName>,<lb/>
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-13">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Your Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                        the receipt of Mr. White’s note of the 19th ultimo, respecting Messrs.
                        Arkell &amp; Douglas’s shipments to South Africa by the <hi rend="italic"
                            >Maria, Mashona</hi>, and the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>A copy of this note and of its inclosures will be forwarded to the high
                        commissioner for South Africa.</p>
                    <p>The observations which I had the honor to make in my note of the 9th instant
                        in regard to Messrs. Peabody &amp; Company’s shipments apply also to the
                        information now supplied in regard to Messrs. Arkell &amp; Douglas.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis Bertie.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
